Package: counselor
Title: Voice-Powered Code Review for Human Oversight of AI-Assisted Development
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Jasmine", "Daly", , "jasmine@dalyanalytics.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Intercepts git commits and engages developers in voice conversations
    to review AI-generated code changes before they proceed. Uses ellmer for
    conversation intelligence with Claude, and Pipecat for voice I/O via Deepgram
    (speech-to-text) and Cartesia (text-to-speech). The developer remains in
    control - nothing commits without explicit approval.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Imports:
    cli,
    ellmer,
    git2r,
    glue,
    jsonlite,
    reticulate
Suggests:
    askpass,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
URL: https://github.com/dalyanalytics/counselor
BugReports: https://github.com/dalyanalytics/counselor/issues
